> - **Damage Immunities** force
> - **Senses** blindsight 10ft., darkvision 60ft., passive Perception 16
> - **Languages** Common, Draconic
> - **Challenge** 14 (11,500 XP)
> ___
>
> ***Legendary Resistance (3/Day).*** If the dragon fails a saving throw, it can choose to succeed instead.
>
> ***Magic Destruction.*** Whenever an enemy creature within 30 feet of the dragon casts a spell, it must make a DC 18 Wisdom saving throw, taking 7 (2d6) psychic damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.
> 
> ***Protector of Magic.*** The dragon senses the presence of magic within 60 feet of it. If it senses magic in this way, it can see a faint aura around any visible creature or object in the area that bears magic, and it learn its school of magic, if any.
>
> ***Innate Spellcasting.*** The dragon's innate spellcasting ability is Intelligence (spell save DC 17, +9 to hit with spell attacks). It can innately cast the following spells, requiring no material components:
> 
> At will: *detect thoughts*, ✦*flurry*, *minor illusion*, *shape  <br/>      water* ^XGE^ 
> <br/> 3/day each: *armor of agathys*, *dispel magic*, *fog cloud*, <br/>     *invisibility*,  *magic missile*
> <br/> 1/day each: ✦*amplify or dampen magic*, ✦*spellsteal*, <br/>     *wall of force*
> 
>
> ### Actions
> ***Multiattack.*** The dragon can use its Frightful Presence. It then makes two attacks: one with its bite and one with its claws.
>
> ***Bite.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* +10 to hit, reach 10ft., one target. *Hit:* 16 (2d10 + 5) piercing damage plus 7 (2d6) cold damage.
>
> ***Claw.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* +10 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. *Hit:* 12 (2d6 + 5) slashing damage.
>
> ***Tail.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* +10 to hit, reach 15ft., one target. *Hit:* 14 (2d8 + 5) bludgeoning damage.
>
> ***Frightful Presence.*** Each creature of the dragon's choice that is within 120 feet of the dragon and aware of it 
>
> must succeed on a DC 18 Wisdom saving throw or become frightened for 1 minute. A creature can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success. If a creature's saving throw is successful or the effect ends for it, the creature is immune to the dragon's Frightful Presence for the next 24 hours.
>
> ***Breath Weapons (Recharge 5-6).*** The dragon uses one of the following breath weapons.
>
> **Spellfrost Breath.** The dragon exhales an icy blast in a 
<br/>    60-foot cone. Each creature in that area must make a 
<br/>    DC 18 Dexterity saving throw, taking 31 (9d6) force 
<br/>    damage plus 17 (5d6) cold damage on a failed save, 
<br/>    or half as much damage on a successful one. 
> <br/> In addition, any creature damaged by the breath must 
<br/>    make a DC 19 Wisdom saving throw or lose spell 
<br/>    slots of combined level 2d4+1, starting with the 
<br/>    highest available level. The target regains any spell 
<br/>    slots lost in this way when they finish a short rest.
> **Repulsion Breath.** The dragon exhales repulsion energy 
<br/>    in a 30-foot cone. Each creature in that area must 
<br/>    make a DC 18 Strength saving throw or be pushed
<br/>    60 feet away from the dragon and they cannot cast
<br/>    any spells until the start of the dragon's next turn.
>
> ***Change Shape.*** The dragon can magically polymorph into a humanoid or back into its true form. It reverts to its true form if it dies. Any equipment it is wearing or carrying is absorbed or borne by the new form (its choice). 
> <br/>    In a new form, the dragon retains its alignment, hit points, ability to speak, proficiencies, Legendary Resistance, Innate Spellcasting and Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma scores, as well as this action.
>
> ### Legendary Actions
> The dragon can take 3 legendary actions, choosing from the options below. Only one legendary action option can be used at a time and only at the end of another creature's turn. The dragon regains spent legendary actions at the start of its turn.
>
> **Spell.** The dragon casts one of its at will spells.
> <br/> **Arcane Vacuum.** Each creature within 40 feet of the 
<br/>    dragon must make a DC 18 Strength saving throw or 
<br/>    be pulled to the closest unoccupied space next to 
<br/>    the dragon.
> <br/> **Spell Control (2 actions).** A creature the dragon can see 
<br/>    within 60 feet must succeed on a DC 18 Wisdom 
<br/>    saving throw or end any concentration spell it is 
<br/>    casting. In addition, it cannot cast concentration 
<br/>    spells until the end of the dragon's next turn.
> <br/> **Wing Attack (Costs 2 Actions).** The dragon beats its 
<br/>    wings. Each creature within 10 feet of the dragon 
<br/>    must succeed on a DC 21 Dexterity saving throw or 
<br/>    take 12 (2d6 + 5) bludgeoning damage and be 
<br/>    knocked prone. The dragon can then fly up to half its 
<br/>    flying speed.

