> ***Bite.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* +8 to hit, reach 10ft., one target. *Hit:* 15 (2d10 + 4) piercing damage plus 9 (2d8) fire damage.
>
> ***Claw.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* +8 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. *Hit:* 13 (2d8 + 4) slashing damage.
>
> ***Breath Weapons (Recharge 5-6).*** The drake uses one of the following breath weapons.
>
> **Searing Sand Breath.** The drake exhales superheated 
<br/>    sand in a 30-foot cone. Each creature in that area 
<br/>    must make a DC 17 Dexterity saving throw, taking 
<br/>    42 (12d6) fire damage on a failed save and 
<br/>    becoming blinded until the end of the drake's next 
<br/>    turn. On a success, a creature take half as much 
<br/>    damage to no other ill effect.  
> **Slowing Breath.** The drake exhales pure temporal energy 
<br/>    in a 30-foot cone. Each creature in that area must 
<br/>    succeed on a DC 16 Constitution saving throw. On a 
<br/>    failed save, the creature can't use reactions, its speed 
<br/>    is halved, and it can't make more than one attack on 
<br/>    its turn. In addition, the creature can use either an 
<br/>    action or a bonus action on its turn, but not both. 
<br/>    These effects last for 1 minute. The creature can 
<br/>    repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its 
<br/>    turns, ending the effect on itself with a successful 
<br/>    save.
>
> ***Change Shape.*** The drake can magically polymorph into a humanoid or back into its true form. It reverts to its true form if it dies. Any equipment it is wearing or carrying is absorbed or borne by the new form (its choice). 
> <br/>     In a new form, the drake retains its alignment, hit points, ability to speak, proficiencies, Innate Spellcasting and Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma scores, as well as this action.


